translated: Englund, Briunio Seved Gösita, county forester, from Visby. Born May 23, 1903 in Gran-gärde, Kopparsberg County. Son of forester Gösta E. and Elsa Tigerhielm. Married in 1934 to Elisabeth Danielson. They had three children: Christina (born 1937), Inger (born 1941), and Carl Seved (born 1943). Englund passed the high school graduation examination in Norrköping in 1921 and graduated from the Forestry School in 1926. He worked as a forest laborer for various domains and private employers from 1926-1929, and then served as a county forester for the domain from 1929-1933, followed by service as a forest assistant for the forest administration in Gotland from 1933-1938. From 1939, he served as deputy county forester and then as county forester from 1948. Englund also served as the manager for the fuel control agency in Gotland from 1940-1947. He was a member of the county council from 1942-1947, a member of the transportation committee for the county road classification from 1942, and a member of the county council's war time committee from 1947.
